column1: #Text=Waukegan is in the Far North Suburbs of the Chicagoland region of Illinois .
#Text=It sits on Lake Michigan , has a large harbor , and is the county seat of Lake County , Illinois .
#Text=Waukegan is located in close proximity to Interstate 94 and US Highway 41 .
#Text=Downtown Waukegan can be accessed from either using Grand Avenue or Washington Street .
#Text=The Union Pacific North Line runs between Kenosha and the Ogilvie Transportation Center in downtown Chicago and serves Waukegan .
#Text=Chicago O'Hare International Airport ( ORD ) is the closest international airport to Waukegan .
#Text=Milwaukee Mitchell International Airport ( MKE ) is the next closest international airport to Waukegan .
#Text=The Genesee Theatre is Lake County 's premier entertainment venue .
#Text=Productions include comedy acts , musicals , classical movies , and concerts .
#Text=Jack Benny Center for the Arts , 39 Jack Benny Dr , ☏ +1847 360-4740 .
#Text=Lake County 's only opera company , costumed and fully staged .
#Text=Featuring Waukegan Symphony Orchestra and Concert Chorus .
#Text=The Jack Benny Center for the Arts is in magnificent Bowen Park .
#Text=The art center is named after Jack Benny , who had a comedy radio/television program in the mid-1900s and was from Waukegan .
